dataset.title: Ag Security Areas
dataset.description:
Metadata

Property Type Codes (TYPE field) 

A – Residential (10 Acres or More)

AA – Agricultural Converted to Apartments

AC – Residential w/ Commercial (10+ Acres)

AL – Vacant Land (10+ Acres) w/ leasehold dwelling

AO – Residential Out-Building only (10+ Acres)

AS – Seasonal-used less than 50% of year

AT – Manufactured Home with 10+ acres

AX – Residential 10+ Acres – Exempt

C – Commercial – General

C1 – Commercial – General ($1 - $99,999)

C2 – Commercial – General ($100,000 - $299,000)

C3 – Commercial – General ($300,000 - $599,000)

C4 – Commercial – General ($600,000 - $999,999)

C5 – Commercial – General ($1,000,000 and above)

CA – Commercial - Apartments (4 or more)

CB – Commercial - Bank

CC – Commercial - Combination

CF – Fraternities and Sororities

CG – Commercial – Service Station

CH – Commercial – Parking Lot

CL – Commercial – Vacant Land

CM – Commercial – Motel, Hotel, Inn, B&B

CP – Commercial – Campground

CQ – Rooming House

CR – Commercial – Restaurant

CS – Commercial – Store

CT – Commercial – Mobile Home Park (4 or More)

CU – Commercial – Utility

CV – Commercial – Convenience Store w/Gas

CX – Commercial – Exempt

CY – Commercial – Golf Course

CZ – Commercial – Minerals

I – Industrial

IL – Industrial – Vacant Land

L1 – Vacant Land (< 1 Acre)

L2 – Vacant Land (1-4.99 Acres)

L3 – Vacant Land (5-9.99 Acres)

LL – Vacant Lot (<10Acres) w/leasehold (No Dwelling)

LX – Vacant Land – Exempt

MA – Mineral – Active

MR – Mineral – Reserve

MX – Mineral – Reserve Exempt

R – Residential (Under 10 Acres)

RA – Residential Converted to Apartments

RC – Residential w/ commercial function

RF – Fraternities and Sororities

RL – Vacant Lot (< 10 Acres) – w/ Leasehold Dwelling

RO – Residential – Out-building Only

RS – Seasonal – Used less than 50% of year

RT – Manufactured Home – w/ land (one Owner)

RX – Residential Land – Exempt

T – Manufactured Home – No Land (Lease Hold)

TX – Mobile Home – Exempt – No Land (lease)

U – Public Utilities (Exempt – Real-estate Taxes)

UX – Public Utilities (Exempt – All Taxes)

V – Vacant Land

VL – Vacant Land (10+ Acres) w/ Leasehold (No Dwelling)

VS – Vacant Land – Subdivision Potential

VX – Vacant Land – Exempt


Clean and Green (CNG field)

Y - Property is enrolled in Clean and Green

N -  Property is not enrolled in Clean and Green


Agricultural Security Area (ASA field)

Y - Parcel is enrolled in the municipality's Agricultural Security Area but not necessarily preserved

N - Parcel is not enrolled in the municipality's Agricultural Security Area


Easement (Easement field)

Clearwater - Land Preserved by Clearwater Conservancy.  These properties may or may not be enrolled in ASA

PACE - Purchased Agricultural Conservation Easement.  These are properties preserved through the State's farmland preservation program administered by Centre County.

PACE / FRPP - State, County, possibly municipal, and Federal funds were used to purchase the easement.  The Federal program is Farm and Ranch Lands Protection Program.


Restricted (Restricted field)

0 - No restrictions, not preserved

1 - restricted, preserved

dataset.title: Streets
dataset.description:
SCL - Street Center Line data with addressing information.  Subtypes have been set p on the FCODE field.

FCODE

  •  1500 - Public Road:  Any Municipal, State, or Federal owned roadway which is open to the public.
  •  1510 - Named Private Road:  Any roadway that services addressable structures located on private property which is not open to the general public.
  •  1520 - Gated Road:  Any gated road, private or public.
  •  1530 - Seasonally Gated Road:  Any gated road, private or public, that is only open during specific times of the year.
  •  1540 - Drivable Trail:  State Forestry, Game Land, Park, or Fish Commission trail.  Primarily 4WD accessible road with little or no maintenance.
  •  1550 - State Public Land Road:  Any State Forestry, Game Land, Park, or Fish & Boat, roadway that is used to access State Public Lands.  Road condition, maintenance, and accessibility are inconsistent.
